Selenium IDE

1) Selenium IDE is an Record and Play plugin for the browser e.g. Firefox, Chrome
2) There are lot of drawback in Selenium IDE
3) It not automate fully just like Selenium webDriver
4) It is use to create simple scripts or assists in exploratory testing
5) How to use Selenium IDE: 
   a) Go to the browser
   b) Open the plugin installer
   c) Search for Selenium IDE and install it
   d) Open the Selenium IDE
   e) Hit on the 'Record a new test in a new project
   f) Provide the project name
   g) Provide the base URl
   h) Hit on the start recording
   i) Perform the test 
   j) Go to the Selenium IDE and hit on the 'Stop the test'
   k) Give the name to the test
   l) Hit on the 'Run all test' to re-excute test again through Selenium IDE
   
Katalon Recorder

1) It is an another extension to the chrome
2) It is little better than Selenium IDE.
3) How to use Katalon Recorder:
   a) Go to the browser
   b) Open the extension for Katalon
   c) Install the extension
   d) Open the Katalon Recorder
   e) Create a new Project and Test
   f) Start the test and perform actions
   g) Stop the test
   h) Hit on the 'Export' button 
   i) Select the format Java (WebDriver + TestNG)